The paper deals with probabilistic model checking, which involves analyzing probabilistic systems. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with Markov chains, which are a type of dynamical system, and perturbation analysis, which involves analyzing the stability of a system under small changes. These topics are relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves computing bounds for probabilities, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
